# Commands

Commands are given through a prefix `\\` followed by the command name like `\\file{}`.
In the brackets one can provide arguments separate through `,`.

## Examples

Loading a file and inserting it into the request at the given position:

```
gpt ask Explain the functions in the following: \\file{/path/to/your/file}
```

Executing the command an parsing the stdout and stderr into the request.

```
gpt ask I get the following output from my program: \\execute{/path/to/your/file}. Can you tell me whats wrong?
```